      <p>Welcome back! Unity Hub should now be done downloading. </p>
         <p> We will now begin to 
          install Unity.</p>
         
          <p>Unity will appear at the bottom of your browser. If it doesn't appear there, check your Downloads folder. If it still
          doesn't appear, give it a few moments and try again. If you are still having
          problems and it is not showing up, try checking the <a href="help">Help Page</a>. </p>
          <p>Is everything looking good? Great!</p>
          <p>Click on the Unity Hub downloader (called UnityHubSetup.exe)</p>
          <p>Once you do, your computer should ask you whether or not you want the app
          to make changes to your device. Click Yes.</p>
          <p>Click Yes only if you get 1. Your parents permission (if you are under age).
          2. Are allowed to run it. </p>
          <p>As we go through the following steps, remember to read through everything.</p>
        <p>Click Next to continue. Read through the Terms of Service, click the box
        to Accept the License Agreement, and click Next. If you want to read the full
        Terms of Service later, go to the <a href="resources">Resources Page</a>.</p>
        
        <p>Next Unity is going to allow you to choose where to install it's location. The location of Unity is going to be the place where all of it's files and your projects will be located at. 
        For the moment, let's leave the location, or Destination Folder, alone. The reason we want to leave this alone is because if we have to look at something that is in Unity's home folder, we can easily look for where it might be online. If we change it, then there is a possibility that we may not remember where it is located at. </p>
        <p>If you want to change where Unity downloads to, you can click Browse.. and
        change its location. Just make sure you remember  where you save everything to!</p>
        
        <p>After you click Next, Unity will begin downloading onto your computer. 
        Just let it do its thing and wait. It will take between 10 minutes to 3 hours (usually less)
        depending on your computer and internet speed.</p>
        
        <p>After it is done, click on Finish and make sure the box for Run Unity Hub is checked.</p>
         
         
